<paragraph id="8B9536CD8129F436FF0674CD4807493F" blockId="11.[136,1451,1778,2093]" lastBlockId="12.[136,1452,158,401]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FF0674CD4C7C4F5F" bold="true" box="[136,351,1778,1804]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FEF574CC4F514F5F" authorityName="Raab-Straube &amp; Greuter" baseAuthorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[379,626,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FEF574CC4F514F5F" box="[379,626,1778,1805]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">Cyanus ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as an endemic species from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D765D8129F431FB0C74CD49F14F5F" box="[1154,1234,1778,1804]" name="Turkey" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">Turkey</collectingCountry>
with the name of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FF0675284CBC4F63" authorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,415,1814,1841]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FF0675284CBC4F63" box="[136,415,1814,1841]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">Centaurea ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C8129F431FE4175294F824F63" author="Sirin, E. &amp; Uysal, T. &amp; Bozkurt, M. &amp; Ertugrul, K." box="[463,673,1814,1840]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" pagination="173 - 179" refId="ref19843" refString="Sirin, E., Uysal, T., Bozkurt, M. &amp; Ertugrul, K. (2020) Centaurea akcadaghensis and C. ermenekensis (Asteracaeae), two new species from Turkey. Mediterranean Botany 41: 173 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.5209 / mbot. 68628" type="journal article" year="2020">
Şirin 
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FD9E75284F6F4F63" box="[528,588,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
and then its name was changed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FBCC7528481B4F63" authorityName="Raab-Straube &amp; Greuter" baseAuthorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1090,1336,1814,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FBCC7528481B4F63" box="[1090,1336,1814,1841]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">Cyanus ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Raab- Straube &amp; Greuter in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C8129F431FEF575054FE74F07" author="Raab-Straube, E. von &amp; Raus, Th." box="[379,708,1850,1877]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" pagination="141 - 168" refId="ref19370" refString="Raab-Straube, E. von &amp; Raus, Th. (Ed.) (2021) Euro + Med-Checklist Notulae, 13 [Notulae ad floram euro-mediterraneam pertinentes No. 42]. Willdenowia 51: 141 - 168. https: // doi. org / 10.3372 / wi. 51.51112" type="journal article" year="2021">Raab-Straube &amp; Raus (2021)</bibRefCitation>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C8129F431FCE6750549114F07" author="Sirin, E. &amp; Uysal, T. &amp; Bozkurt, M. &amp; Ertugrul, K." box="[872,1074,1850,1876]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" pagination="173 - 179" refId="ref19843" refString="Sirin, E., Uysal, T., Bozkurt, M. &amp; Ertugrul, K. (2020) Centaurea akcadaghensis and C. ermenekensis (Asteracaeae), two new species from Turkey. Mediterranean Botany 41: 173 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.5209 / mbot. 68628" type="journal article" year="2020">
Şirin 
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FC2875044EFD4F07" box="[934,990,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FBB3750449D64F07" authorityName="Raab-Straube &amp; Greuter" baseAuthorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1085,1269,1850,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FBB3750449D64F07" box="[1085,1269,1850,1877]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">C. ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FF4975604C4B4F2B" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[199,360,1887,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuterianus">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FF4975604C4B4F2B" box="[199,360,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">C. reuterianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its stem, number of capitula, involucre, and median appendages. Based on the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FF0675BC4C624FCF" authorityName="Raab-Straube &amp; Greuter" baseAuthorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[136,321,1922,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FF0675BC4C624FCF" box="[136,321,1922,1949]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">C. ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its comparison with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8129F431FDEF75BC4E204FCF" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[609,771,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuterianus">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FDEF75BC4E204FCF" box="[609,771,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">C. reuterianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C8129F431FCFB75BD49614FCF" author="Sirin, E. &amp; Uysal, T. &amp; Bozkurt, M. &amp; Ertugrul, K." box="[885,1090,1922,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" pagination="173 - 179" refId="ref19843" refString="Sirin, E., Uysal, T., Bozkurt, M. &amp; Ertugrul, K. (2020) Centaurea akcadaghensis and C. ermenekensis (Asteracaeae), two new species from Turkey. Mediterranean Botany 41: 173 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.5209 / mbot. 68628" type="journal article" year="2020">
Şirin 
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8129F431FC3A75BC4ECE4FCF" box="[948,1005,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
, and my careful examination of the important morphological traits (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C8129F431FDAC75994FF34F92" author="Wagenitz, G." box="[546,720,1958,1985]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" pagination="465 - 585" refId="ref20808" refString="Wagenitz, G. (1975) Centaurea L. In: Davis, P. H. (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, vol. 5. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, pp. 465 - 585." type="book chapter" year="1975">Wagenitz 1975</bibRefCitation>
) of the 
<typeStatus id="5491886F8129F431FCBE75984E434F92" box="[816,864,1959,1985]" pageId="11" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
specimens, I found noticeable similarities, namely flowering stem lateral at base of a rosette, usually arising from base of rosette, simple or branched in upper part, decumbent-ascending, cauline leaves lanceolate to oblanceolate, 1.8–2.9 × 
<quantity id="4CD29B288129F431FC6075D14951405A" box="[1006,1138,2030,2057]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.9 cm</quantity>
, capitula solitary at end of stem and branches, involucres ovoid and 
<quantity id="4CD29B288129F431FDDC7A2D4FE9407E" box="[594,714,2066,2093]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="15.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="12.0">12–18 mm</quantity>
long, median appendages ovate-oblong, peripheral florets slightly radiant, central florets pink- to violet-purple, 
<quantity id="4CD29B28812EF436FDF172A14FD448EA" box="[639,759,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16 mm</quantity>
long, achenes ovoid-oblong, 3.5–4.5 × 
<quantity id="4CD29B28812EF436FB2172A1480148EA" box="[1199,1314,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
, and pappus scabrous. The only difference is that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812EF436FDA872FC4FFE488F" authorityName="Raab-Straube &amp; Greuter" baseAuthorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[550,733,194,221]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812EF436FDA872FC4FFE488F" box="[550,733,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">C. ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has narrower involucres and slightly smaller appendages, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812EF436FF0672D84C094953" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[136,298,231,257]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuterianus">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812EF436FF0672D84C094953" box="[136,298,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">C. reuterianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has wider involucres and slightly larger appendages, but following a thorough investigation of many specimens, I concluded the variation in the involucres and appendages to be continuous. Therefore, by comparing localities and geographical distributions (
<figureCitation id="13112A48812EF436FDD973114FB9491A" box="[599,666,302,329]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1216,1238]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,460,1156]" captionTargetId="figure-125@12.[164,1423,425,1192]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution of Cyanus reuterianus var. reuterianus (circles), C. reuterianus var. phrygius (squares), and C. raimondoi (triangle) in Turkey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5843487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5843487/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), and comparing with other samples and 
<typeStatus id="5491886F812EF436FBEB731049B6491A" box="[1125,1173,303,329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
specimens, I established that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812EF436FF37736C4C52493F" authorityName="Raab-Straube &amp; Greuter" baseAuthorityName="Uysal &amp; Sirin" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[185,369,338,365]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ermenekensis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812EF436FF37736C4C52493F" box="[185,369,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">C. ermenekensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
did not differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812EF436FDC1736C4FD3493F" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[591,752,339,365]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuterianus">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812EF436FDC1736C4FD3493F" box="[591,752,339,365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">C. reuterianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and should be considered as a new synonym of it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3306546812EF436FF3373494E6A49C3" box="[189,841,374,401]" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9536CD812EF436FF3373494E6A49C3" blockId="12.[136,1452,158,401]" box="[189,841,374,401]" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812EF436FF3373494C7A49C3" bold="true" box="[189,345,374,400]" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812EF436FEFB73484F7349C3" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[373,592,375,401]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuterianus">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812EF436FEFB73484F7349C3" box="[373,592,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">Cyanus reuterianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F33D765D812EF436FD7D73494E6649C3" box="[755,837,374,400]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="30">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
